description:
Trigger: a downstream user wants to log or print their backend instance for diagnostics: tracing::debug!(?backend, "signing operation").

Bad behavior: secretx-pkcs11/src/lib.rs:46-55 declares pub struct Pkcs11Backend with no derive(Debug) and no manual impl. Compile error at the call site. Users will work around with format!('{:?}', ...) -> can't, ad-hoc Display impls, or just stop logging.

Why it's missing: cryptoki::context::Pkcs11 may not be Debug. The user_pin field must NOT be Debug-printed (security). Hence the struct can't blanket-derive.

Fix: write a manual Debug impl that prints slot, label (the structural identifiers), and 'lib loaded' / 'pin set: <bool>' for the security-sensitive fields. Example:

impl std::fmt::Debug for Pkcs11Backend {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
        f.debug_struct("Pkcs11Backend")
            .field("slot", &self.slot)
            .field("label", &self.label)
            .field("pin_set", &self.user_pin.is_some())
            .finish_non_exhaustive()
    }
}
